NYANGA cops are investigating a murder after ward 36 Councillor Nokuthula Bolitye (50) was shot dead outside her home in Old Crossroads, Cape Town on Monday, 12 July. Warrant Officer Joseph Swartbooi said police are looking for clues after the victim was shot and killed in Gqolomba Street in Old Crossroads. “According to reports, the victim was seated in a minibus taxi in front of her home when three unknown men approached the vehicle and fired numerous gunshots at the victim,” said Swartbooi. He said the suspects fled the scene and are yet to be arrested. Anyone with information is urged to call CrimeStop on 08600 10111. Vuyisile Tyhalisisu from the ANC in the Dullar Omar region said they are shocked to learn about the brutal killing of its deployee to the City of Cape Town. He said Bolitye was elected as a councillor for ward 36 in the City of Cape Town on 12 July. “This was not the first attempt on Bolitye’s life. She has survived another attempt on her life in 2020,” said Tyhalisisu. He condemns this barbaric and cowardly act and has called on the police to work tirelessly to apprehend those responsible. City of Cape Town mayor Dan Plato extended his condolences to Bolitye’s family. “I am saddened to hear of the tragic passing of one of our city’s ward councillor. I wish her family, friends, colleagues, and all who knew her strength during this period of grief,” said Plato. Plato said Bolitye has been a ward councillor for the past five years.